modules.description: This module offers functions for creating and customizing 2D and 3D visualizations, including line, scatter, histogram, and surface plots, along with annotations and layout adjustments. It operates on numerical matrices (`dsmat`) and vectors, supporting advanced configurations for axes, colors, and output formats. Applications include statistical analysis, scientific data visualization, and displaying probability distributions or sparse data structures.

This module defines core types and constants for numerical computations, including number types (float32, float64, complex32, complex64), index and slice representations for tensor operations, and device types (CPU, OpenCL, CUDA). It supports precise array slicing and memory layout configurations, enabling efficient numerical processing in Jupyter environments. Use cases include tensor indexing, device-specific memory allocation, and numerical type dispatch in high-performance computing workflows.
